AstrOsEspNowProtocol
====================

Pure, native-testable decoder for ESP-NOW packets already validated by
AstrOsMessaging. Turns a parsed astros_packet_t into a
HandlerResult — either an InterfaceMessage ready for the interface
queue, a Pending signal for multi-packet reassembly, or a diagnostic
for the MIXED adapter (AstrOsEspNow) to log at the boundary.

Parallel to AstrOsSerialProtocol: same rich-return pattern, same
caller-logs-at-the-boundary contract. Does not touch peer state,
registration, or the poll cycle — those remain in AstrOsEspNow pending
a separate extraction.

Purity rule
-----------

This library is unit-tested on the native host under [env:test], so it
must not include any of:

    freertos/*, esp_*, driver/*, nvs_*, sdmmc_*, esp_vfs*, esp_now*, esp_wifi*

Enforced by the CI purity guard in .github/workflows/pr-validation.yml.

Error-channel convention
------------------------

Functions return HandlerResult with a HandlerStatus enum and an
optional diagnostic string. No logging — the MIXED adapter
(AstrOsEspNow) logs the diagnostic at ESP_LOGE when status is an error
variant.
